        This allows a StateInternals implementation to start an asynchronous prefetch or to include this state in the next batch of reads.

      • read

        public OutputT read()
        Description copied from interface: ReadableState
        Read the current value, blocking until it is available.

        If there will be many calls to ReadableState.read() for different state in short succession, you should first call ReadableState.readLater() for all of them so the reads can potentially be batched (depending on the underlying StateInternals implementation}.

        Specified by:
